▁since ▁the ▁edo ▁period ▁it ▁has ▁been ▁counted ▁as ▁one ▁of ▁japan ▁' s ▁three ▁scenic ▁views ▁, ▁along ▁with ▁matsushima ▁( ▁current ▁miyagi ▁prefecture ▁) ▁and ▁miya jima ▁( ▁current ▁hiroshima ▁prefecture ▁) ▁.
