▁furthermore ▁, ▁when ▁a ▁permanent ▁right ▁to ▁charge ▁yak usen ▁( ▁ 役銭 ▁) ▁from ▁doso ▁( ▁ 土倉 ▁) ▁and ▁sakaya ▁( ▁ 酒 屋 ▁) ▁in ▁kyoto ▁was ▁allowed ▁during ▁the ▁era ▁of ▁yoshimitsu ▁ashikaga ▁, ▁yak usen ▁were ▁charged ▁together ▁with ▁t ansen ▁, ▁mun ab etsu - sen ▁, ▁etc ▁. ▁, ▁by ▁the ▁doso ▁appointed ▁by ▁bakufu ▁, ▁who ▁were ▁referred ▁to ▁as ▁no sen - kata ▁.
▁no sen - kata ▁were ▁later ▁also ▁entrusted ▁with ▁clerical ▁matters ▁such ▁as ▁the ▁safe ke eping ▁/ ▁book ke eping ▁of ▁tax ▁income ▁, ▁and ▁such ▁doso ▁were ▁referred ▁to ▁as ▁kubo - okura ▁( ▁ 公 方 御 倉 ▁) ▁.
