▁during ▁the ▁early ▁heian ▁period ▁, ▁chinese ▁poetry ▁overwhelmed ▁waka ▁as ▁a ▁public ▁literature ▁.
▁z oto ka ▁( ▁poems ▁exchanged ▁between ▁a ▁man ▁and ▁a ▁woman ▁) ▁became ▁the ▁leading ▁style ▁of ▁waka ▁, ▁and ▁the ▁number ▁of ▁waka ▁composed ▁in ▁the ▁imperial ▁court ▁decreased ▁compared ▁with ▁that ▁of ▁the ▁nara ▁period ▁.
