▁intellectual ▁and ▁ideal ▁styles ▁of ▁poetry ▁are ▁characteristic ▁of ▁this ▁collection ▁.
▁fifty ▁years ▁later ▁, ▁in ▁the ▁reign ▁of ▁emperor ▁murakami ▁, ▁wak ad okoro ▁( ▁bureau ▁of ▁poetry ▁) ▁was ▁established ▁, ▁where ▁n ashitsu bo ▁no ▁gon in ▁( ▁five ▁men ▁of ▁the ▁pear ▁chamber ▁) ▁read ▁the ▁chinese ▁characters ▁in ▁" ▁manyoshu ▁, ▁" ▁which ▁was ▁already ▁difficult ▁to ▁read ▁at ▁that ▁time ▁, ▁in ▁the ▁japanese ▁pronunciation ▁, ▁and ▁compiled ▁and ▁dedicated ▁" ▁go sen ▁wakashu ▁( ▁later ▁collection ▁of ▁japanese ▁poetry ▁) ▁" ▁to ▁the ▁emperor ▁.
