▁this ▁theory ▁was ▁originated ▁by ▁shinto ▁people ▁who ▁had ▁complain ed ▁about ▁buddhism ▁, ▁which ▁had ▁been ▁dominant ▁over ▁shinto ▁, ▁and ▁wanted ▁shinto ▁to ▁achieve ▁independent ▁status ▁from ▁it ▁.
▁the ▁wat arai ▁clan ▁, ▁who ▁had ▁served ▁as ▁priests ▁of ▁ge gu ▁( ▁the ▁outer ▁shrine ▁of ▁ise ▁jingo ▁) ▁organized ▁and ▁re - ed ited ▁myths ▁and ▁the ▁records ▁of ▁shinto ▁ceremonies ▁in ▁order ▁to ▁compile ▁the ▁shinto ▁go busho ▁( ▁five - volume ▁apolog ia ▁of ▁shinto ▁) ▁; ▁their ▁work ▁laid ▁the ▁foundation ▁for ▁ise ▁wat arai ▁shinto ▁.
